Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees.

Heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve @red grapes{2.25%ounce}. Halve, core and dice @apple{1}(core and dice into bite-size pieces).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine grapes, apple, and @apricot jam{1%unit}; toss until fruit is coated. Set aside until ready to serve.

Place @cream cheese{1/2%cup} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until softened, ~{30-45%seconds}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Submerge closed cream cheese packets in a bowl of warm water to soften.

Whisk in @brown sugar{1%unit} until no lumps remain.

In a #wide shallow bowl{}, whisk @eggs{2}, half the @milk{1%unit}, half the @cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} until well combined (all the milk and 2 TBSP white sugar for 4 servings).

Spread one side of each @sourdough bread{4%slice} slice with cream cheese mixture. Top half the sourdough slices with bacon. Close sandwiches with remaining sourdough slices, coated sides down.

Wash out bowl used for cream cheese mixture.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for bacon over medium heat.

Dip sandwiches in egg mixture, gently flipping a few times to coat.

When butter begins to foam, add sandwiches to pan, letting excess egg mixture drip back into bowl. Cook, lightly pressing with a #spatula{}, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (Work in batches if necessary; wipe out pan and add more oil and butter between batches. The second batch may take less time.)

Transfer French toast to a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}; bake on top rack until filling is custardy, ~{6-8%minutes}.

In bowl used for cream cheese mixture, combine @maple syrup{4%tablespoon}, remaining cinnamon, and @butter{1%tablespoon}; cover with plastic wrap.

Microwave until butter has melted, ~{30-45%seconds}. Carefully uncover and stir to combine.

Halve French toast and divide between #plates{}. Drizzle with cinnamon maple syrup and sprinkle with @almonds{1/2%ounce}.

Serve with fruit salad on the side.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.